vcstack.name: vcstack

revisions.description: Added disabled master monitoring object and a new resiliency-link status
MIB revision history dates in descriptions updated.
OID of vcstackTraps was reverted to 6 but deprecated. Added vcstackNotifications
Changed the OID value of vcstackTraps from 6 to 0 to meet RFC 3584 3.1
Obsoleted fallback-config, added new status object
Added stack master object and corrected allowable ranges for learned neighbour stack ID's.

vcstackReadinessStatus.name: vcstackReadinessStatus
vcstackReadinessStatus.description: Indicates how readily a stack member can take over as master if the current stack master were to fail. Possible values are: init (1) - the stack member is completing startup initialization. syncing (2) - the stack member is synchronizing state information with the stack master following startup. ready (3) - the stack member is fully synchronized with the current master and is ready to take over immediately. syncError (4) - state information on the stack member is not correctly synchronized with the current stack master. For a stack member to take over as stack master with the least possible network disruption, it must have the 'ready (3)' status.
